3029541, \"rank\": 0.1718833164326029, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sport|Olympics Adam Burgessbanished\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 264}, {\"ngram\": \"the sleepless nights\", \"from\": 265, \"to\": 285}, {\"ngram\": \"their superb\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 346}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympics\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 368}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Burgessclaimed a stunning silver in the men's single, three years after missing out on a medal by an agonising margin of just 0.16seconds.\", \"from\": 372, \"to\": 510, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a stunning silver\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 404}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 466}, {\"ngram\": \"an agonising margin\", \"from\": 470, \"to\": 489}, {\"ngram\": \"just 0.16seconds\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 509}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There'll be no waking up in the night, wondering what could have been now,\\\" said the 32-year-old.\", \"from\": 512, \"to\": 610, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the night\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 550}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I really wanted to just leave it all out there today.\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 665, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have paid the price and missed opportunities by being a little cautious at times.\", \"from\": 667, \"to\": 751, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the price\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 689}, {\"ngram\": \"missed opportunities\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 714}, {\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 745, \"to\": 750}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And I really wanted to just go out with confidence.\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 803, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"confidence\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 802}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A lot of people were saying I had to be lucky and I was maybe not the one that was talked about for winning a medal.\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 922, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A lot\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 811}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 821}, {\"ngram\": \"the one\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 879}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 921}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That gave me a bit of more grit to go and prove people wrong today.\\\"\", \"from\": 923, \"to\": 991, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bit\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 941}, {\"ngram\": \"more grit\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 954}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 977}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Burgess was just outside the medal places in qualifying, having been fourth-fastest in the afternoon's semi-finals, but produced a superb run when it mattered to finish runner-up behind home favourite Nicolas Gestin.\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 1209, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1194, \"end\": 1208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Gestin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicolas Gestin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Gestin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Gestin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Burgess\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 1000}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal places\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1034}, {\"ngram\": \"qualifying\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1048}, {\"ngram\": \"the afternoon's semi\", \"from\": 1080, \"to\": 1100}, {\"ngram\": \"finals\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1107}, {\"ngram\": \"a superb run\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1134}, {\"ngram\": \"runner-up\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1171}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1183}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympics 2024 medal table: Latest count today after Team GB rush on day three Afterwards, he revealed being inspired by teammate Kimberley Woods, who had been only 12th-fastest in the women's heats on the opening day of the Games before upping her game in the semis and final to grab bronze.\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1503, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1263, \"end\": 1270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999436113, \"rank\": 5.5911953615427055e-11, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1341, \"end\": 1356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kimberley Woods\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympics 2024 medal table\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1236}, {\"ngram\": \"Latest count\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1250}, {\"ngram\": \"day\", \"from\": 1279, \"to\": 1282}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's heats\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1408}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening day\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1427}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1440}, {\"ngram\": \"her game\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1463}, {\"ngram\": \"the semis\", \"from\": 1467, \"to\": 1476}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1501}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was thinking about Kimberley, who made a similar error yesterday and charged up and got herself on to the podium,\\\" he added. \\\"\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1527, \"end\": 1536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Walsh\", \"score\": 0.9999954186974159, \"rank\": 2.293040997811614e-06, \"text\": \"Kimberley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Walsh\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a similar error\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1562}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 1610, \"to